cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with instance segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new framework that leverages the reciprocal relationship between detection and segmentation, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and fully convolutional branches, which are common in natural language processing (NLP) and multimedia (MM) tasks, making cs.CL and cs.MM possible sub-categories.
